 BY BENEDICT NWACHUKWU, ABUJA The All Progressives Congress (APC) Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) has released the schedule of activities for the February 26, 2022 National Convention of the party. The CECPC at its 19th regular meeting on Wednesday at the party’s national secretariat, Buhari House, in Abuja, considered and adopted the timetable/schedule of activities for the convention. A statement from the office of the national secretary indicates that the CECPC will be receiving the Interim Report of the National Reconciliation Committee on January 31, 2022. This will be followed by a consideration and adoption of Reports of State Congresses on February 2, 2022. On February 3, State Executives will be inaugurated. Sales of forms to all aspirants vying for national offices of the party will commence at the party’s secretariat on February 14, 2022. Submission of completed forms and accompanying documents at the APC secretariat will take place on or before February 19, 2022. On the same day, the party will publish the names of sub-committees and their members. Screening of all aspirants vying for National Offices will take place between February 20 and 22, 2022. Screening Appeals to hear and resolve complaints arising from the screening exercise will be on February 23, 2022. Accreditation of all statutory and elected delegates to the National Convention will be on February 24 and 25, 2022, while the National Convention to elect national officers to the National Executive Committee (NEC) is February 26, 2022. National Convention Appeal to hear and resolve complaints arising from the National Convention will sit on February 28, 2022. 